PN,31501
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FThe government will pause
OL,8,Fcryptocurrency donations to political
OL,9,Fparties and introduce a cap on the
OL,10,Famount British dual nationals can
OL,11,Fdonate in efforts to combat foreign
OL,12,Finterference in UK politics.
OL,14,FThe announcement comes after the
OL,15,Fpublication of a review into the issue
OL,16,Fby Phillip Rycroft, which was
OL,17,Fcommissioned in December by Housing
OL,18,Fand Communities Secretary Steve Reed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FThis followed the conviction last year
OL,8,Fof Reform UK's former leader in Wales
OL,9,Ffor accepting bribes from Russia.
OL,11,FNathan Gill, 52, of Anglesey, North
OL,12,FWales, was sentenced last year after
OL,13,Fpreviously pleading guilty to eight
OL,14,Fcounts of bribery.
OL,16,FWriting in his report, Phillip Rycroft
OL,17,Fsaid: "This country faces a persistent
OL,18,Fproblem of foreign interests seeking
OL,19,Fto exert influence on, and to
OL,20,Finterfere in, our politics."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FHe nevertheless urged caution,
OL,8,Fclaiming he was "not pressing the
OL,9,Fpanic button", but "ringing the alarm
OL,10,Fbell".
OL,12,FRycroft made 17 recommendations to the
OL,13,Fgovernment, including urging the
OL,14,Fgovernment to clamp down on
OL,15,Fcryptocurrency donations as well as
OL,16,Fintroduce caps and tighter
OL,17,Frestrictions on the size of donations
OL,18,Fthat can be made.
OL,26,@pD@QOUqD@MO]qD@TOUrD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FStopping short of an outright ban,
OL,8,FRycroft recommended that the
OL,9,Fgovernment legislate to pause
OL,10,Fcryptocurrency donations to political
OL,11,Fparties until the "regulatory
OL,12,Fenvironment can catch up with the
OL,13,Freality of cryptoassets".
OL,15,FHe warned: "There is a risk that
OL,16,Fcryptoassets are used as the vehicle
OL,17,Fto channel foreign money into the
OL,18,Fpolitical system in the UK."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FCryptocurrency donations are legal,
OL,8,Fbut campaign groups such as Spotlight
OL,9,Fon Corruption and Transparency
OL,10,FInternational have warned that the
OL,11,Fanonymity they provide could enable
OL,12,Fdonations from foreign sources.
OL,14,FThe Joint Committee on the National
OL,15,FSecurity Strategy (JCNSS) last month
OL,16,Fdescribed their presence in UK
OL,17,Fpolitics as "unnecessary and
OL,18,Funacceptably high risk to the
OL,19,Fintegrity of the political finance
OL,20,Fsystem and public trust in it."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FFew parties accept crypto donations,
OL,8,Fwith Reform UK being the most
OL,9,Fprominent.
OL,11,FSpeaking to reporters, Rycroft said he
OL,12,Fhad spoken to Reform UK while
OL,13,Fcompiling the report.
OL,15,FAsked about the prospect of Reform
OL,16,Ffeeling targeted by the crypto
OL,17,Frecommendation, he said: "I wasn't
OL,18,Fhere to look out for the interests of
OL,19,Fany political party, I was here to
OL,20,Flook out for the interests of our
OL,21,Fdemocratic processes."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FSpeaking in the Commons, Reed said
OL,8,Fthis pause would be implemented
OL,9,Fretrospectively from Wednesday once
OL,10,Fapproved by parliament.
OL,12,FConcerns have also been raised about
OL,13,Flarge donations being made to
OL,14,Fpolitical parties by dual British-
OL,15,Fforeign nationals, as well as the
OL,16,Fpossibility of foreign individuals
OL,17,Fmaking political donations through
OL,18,FBritish shell companies, as had been
OL,19,Fsuggested Elon Musk may do when
OL,20,Fvoicing support for Farage's Reform UK
OL,21,Flast year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FRycroft suggested reforms to tackle
OL,8,Fboth of these issues.
OL,10,FOn the issue of dual British nationals
OL,11,Fmaking large political donations,
OL,12,FRycroft suggested a cap of between
OL,13,F#100,000 to #300,000 pounds per year.
OL,15,F"This would still allow generous
OL,16,Fdonations over an electoral cycle, but
OL,17,Fwould prevent very large foreign
OL,18,Fdonations slipping through that might
OL,19,Fhave a game-changing impact on
OL,20,Fpolitics in the UK," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FThis recommendation would be
OL,8,Fimmediately accepted from Wednesday,
OL,9,FReed told MPs.
OL,11,FLast year, tech billionaire and owner
OL,12,Fof social media platform X was
OL,13,Freported to have been considering a
OL,14,Fdonation of #80 million to Reform UK.
OL,16,FAccording to the rules, Musk, an
OL,17,FAmerican citizen from South Africa,
OL,18,Fwould not be allowed to make donations
OL,19,Fof more than #500 to UK political
OL,20,Fparties, but there are loopholes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FUK election rules state parties can
OL,8,Fonly accept donations from
OL,9,F"permissible sources". The key
OL,10,Frequirement is being "registered" in
OL,11,Fthe UK.
OL,13,FWith this requirement, Musk would, in
OL,14,Ftheory, be able to donate to political
OL,15,Fparties through the British wing of
OL,16,Fhis social media company X.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FWith this in mind, and with a view to
OL,8,Fforeign individuals using shell
OL,9,Fcompanies to funnel money to political
OL,10,Fparties, Rycroft recommended that no
OL,11,Fcompany should be able to donate more
OL,12,Fmoney to a party than they report as
OL,13,Ftaxable profits for that year.
OL,15,FStarmer responded at the start of last
OL,16,Fyear to repeated attacks by Elon Musk
OL,17,Fon UK politics and his premiership
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31512
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FWhilst Rycroft's review made explicit
OL,8,Freference to hostile states like
OL,9,FRussia and Iran, he also highlighted
OL,10,Fthe detrimental effects of actions
OL,11,Fcoming from some of the UK's allies.
OL,13,F"Beyond these hostile state threats, I
OL,14,Fam also cognisant of a potential new
OL,15,Fthreat: an emerging willingness of
OL,16,Fforeign actors and private citizens,
OL,17,Fincluding from allies like the United
OL,18,FStates, to interfere in, and
OL,19,Finfluence, politics abroad in pursuit
OL,20,Fof their own agenda."
OL,26,@|D@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31513
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FThe UK is already experiencing
OL,8,F"information warfare" and "our
OL,9,Fdefences are worryingly weak," Rycroft
OL,10,Fwarned.
OL,12,FHis report said foreign actors are
OL,13,Fsubverting the debate on social media
OL,14,F"to exacerbate division and increase
OL,15,Fpolarisation with a view simply to
OL,16,Fdestroying the capacity of the UK to
OL,17,Ffunction as a wellgoverned state".
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@UO]pD@[OUqD@^O]vD@AOUyD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31514
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1774480286
OL,3,CGovernment will pause crypto donations
OL,4,Cto stop foreign interference in
OL,5,Celections
OL,7,FRycroft categorised these threats as
OL,8,Feither "attempts to directly suborn
OL,9,Fthe political process through
OL,10,Ffinancial interference", or "sustained
OL,11,Fefforts to undermine trust in
OL,12,Fdemocracy by stoking divisive debate,
OL,13,Fprincipally on social media."
OL,15,FElon Musk was not explicitly named in
OL,16,FRycroft's report, but concerns arose
OL,17,Flast year when the billionaire began
OL,18,Fregularly attacking Starmer on his
OL,19,Fsocial media platform X.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
